{
  "stem": "5810.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- as I told you, it was very important to assimilate.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't want to be pointed out as a stranger or an immigrant.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I did not have a real-- I had a trade, but in the Unites States I found out that the unions were very strong, especially in the textile factory.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to apply in the textile factory, you had to be part of a union.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To be part of a union, you had to have a job in a textile factory.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that didn't work out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And not knowing the language, not having a trade I could get into, I had to start my life all over again.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And not being able to speak English, I had to find something that didn't require the language.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So to make a long story short, I started my life over as a delivery boy for a grocery store chain.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In New York.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, my sister, when she first came to the United States, lived in Philadelphia and then went on to New York.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's what my, my first view of the United States was, New York City, in Manhattan.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I became, as I said, a delivery boy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And from that, I mean, it was such a drastic change to what I had built for myself again, that I decided that I, I just wasn't going to stay here.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And six months later I had a ticket to go back to Belgium and I was going to go back to my job, and what I knew best, and so on.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's when I-- the last thing that I did, somebody had told me about a, a French ball, a dance that was being held at the Statler Hotel in New York.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
